As a JIRA/Confluence/JIRA Agile user I want to be able to have better configuration control on pages that I create in Confluence using information from JIRA so that I can satisfy configuration management requirements of our projects.

We are trying to use Confluence to write Product Requirements Documents that need to be under configuration control. Since all of our requirements are items in a JIRA Agile product backlog I want to use the text in the item as the description in the requirements doc. I have good management of the text on the Confluence page, but if I use any macros that get content from JIRA I don’t have any control. If I could use a query that got information from JIRA on a specific date I would then be able to control when I updated information in my spec.

I currently use JIRA filters to be able to alert people that content in the page may have changed, but there is no way I can recreate the content of a Confluence page without creating a .pdf snapshot of the page.

